-- product_return_rates.sql
SELECT 
    COALESCE(c.name, 'Uncategorized') AS category_name,
    COUNT(oi.item_id) AS total_items_sold,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE 
        WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL 
        THEN oi.item_id 
    END) AS total_items_returned,
    ROUND(
        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE 
            WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL 
            THEN oi.item_id 
        END)::NUMERIC / COUNT(oi.item_id),
        4
    ) AS return_rate
FROM order_items oi
JOIN orders o ON oi.order_id = o.order_id
LEFT JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id
LEFT JOIN categories c ON p.category_id = c.category_id
LEFT JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT 
        item_id, 
        return_id
    FROM returns
    WHERE status = 'approved'
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY item_id ORDER BY return_date DESC) = 1
) r ON oi.item_id = r.item_id
GROUP BY c.name
ORDER BY category_name;
